entry.et: Middle English, from Old English; akin to Old High German westar to the west and probably to Latin vesper evening, Greek hesperos

def.dt: :situated toward or at the west the west exit
:coming from the west a west wind
:the general direction of sunset :the direction to the left of one facing north
:the compass point directly opposite to east
:regions or countries lying to the west of a specified or implied point of orientation
:the noncommunist countries of Europe and America
:the end of a church opposite the chancel
:the one of four positions at 90-degree intervals that lies to the west or at the left of a diagram
:a person (as a bridge player) occupying this position during a specified activity
Nathanael 1903–1940 originally Nathan Wallenstein Weinstein Am. nov.
Dame Rebecca 1892–1983 pseud. of Cicily Isabel Andrews née Fairfield Eng. critic & nov.
:a compass point that is one point north of due west :N78°45′W
:a compass point that is one point south of due west :S78°45′W
